did.head: Collection Summary
did.unittitle: David Dunsford collection of ABC and CBS network television press releases 1962-1970

corpname.part: Moving Image Research Center, National Audio-Visual Conservation Center, Library of Congress, Library of Congress

did.abstract: This collection contains photocopies of original press releases released by the American television networks ABC and CBS between June 11, 1962 and July 4, 1970. The original press releases were collected by David A. Dunsford. The press releases pertain to news programs, television specials, documentaries, movies of the week, religious programs, variety shows, talk shows, soap operas, news programming, dramas, and situation comedies broadcast by ABC and CBS.
did.physloc: A-1557 (box 1) to A-1568 (box 12). Boxes are located in DC, adjacent to the NBC Press Releases.

prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: [Container number, eg., Box 3], David Dunsford Collection, National Audio-Visual Conservation Center, Library of Congress, Library of Congress.

bioghist.head: Organizational Note
bioghist.p: The American Broadcasting Company (ABC) was founded in 1943 from the assets of the National Broadcasting Company (NBC) Blue Network. Television network operations commenced in 1948.

The Columbia Broadcasting System (CBS) was founded in 1929 as a radio broadcasting network. Television operations began in 1931 with the establishment of experimental station W2XAB in New York City. W2XAB received a commercial license as WCBW (later renamed WCBS) in 1941. Television network operations commenced in 1948.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: This collection contains photocopies of original press releases released by the American television networks ABC and CBS between June 11, 1962 and July 4, 1970. The original press releases were collected by David A. Dunsford. The press releases pertain to news programs, television specials, documentaries, movies of the week, religious programs, variety shows, talk shows, soap operas, news programming, dramas, and situation comedies broadcast by ABC and CBS.

arrangement.head: Collection Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged in 2 series:

Records are organized by network (ABC, CBS) and alphabetically thereunder. Press releases pertaining to each individual program, special, or series are organized in distinct folders and indicate date or date range of press releases in parenthesis.
